-- Giants Defeat Phillies 3-0, Take 2-1 Lead in National League Championship
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2010-10-19T23:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/giants-defeat-phillies-3-0-take-2-1-lead-in-national-league-championship.html
Matt Cain allowed two hits in seven
scoreless innings and the San Francisco Giants defeated the
Phillies 3-0, taking a 2-1 lead over Philadelphia in the
National League Chanmpionship Series.  Cody Ross, Aubrey Huff and Freddy Sanchez had run-scoring
singles for the Giants, who are trying to end the Phillies’ two-
year run as National League champions.  Cain outdueled Philadelphia’s Cole Hamels, who had won all
four of his previous postseason road starts.  Game 4 in the best-of-seven series is set for tomorrow
night in San Francisco, with Joe Blanton scheduled to start for
the Phillies against 21-year-old Giants rookie Madison
Bumgarner.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  